			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I am 42nd level Wizard at Realm Rank 2 Level 4. 23k Realm Points. 
<br />

<br />
For RvR.
<br />

<br />
#1. Stay in the back.  by going to the front you will die.  Stay in the back and do as I call "Support Fire" Basically anyone who gets into f8 (nearest monster) range is your target.  First Dot if you have, then DD, DD, DD, untill it drops, then move on to your next target.
<br />

<br />
#2. If you get charged, Quick Cast Root and Run.  No one will pick aggro off of you.  If another friend hits it, it will still come for you, so let your friend hit it while it chases you.
<br />

<br />
#3 Keep Defence.  Peek throw an arrow slit in wall, find a target and destroy it.  If it is a caster, then that is Number one target.  #2 target is a healing class. (Shamens are always #1 on KOS for a Wizard)  #3 anything in range.  If you are an Earth Wizard, Just AE Root everything.  everyone around you, NPC and PC will love you and tell you how much easier it made the defence go. Ice wizards use PBAE from behind doors and walls.  Make sure you have a cleric/friar with cure poison and lots of healing watching you.
<br />

<br />
#4 Attacking a keep.  You are great against NPC Guards. Why? because it is just as dumb as another mob and can aggrod off of you.  so Fire Away on any NPC.  When attacking a keep, Destroy NPC's First, they cannot be rezzed, and are limited in their retaliation.   when everything is cleared off the walls, you may aide the door breaking by casting a few DD's on the gate.  It will not do much damage, and it consume your power, just cast until you get a critical and quite while you are ahead.  Do not charge the Lord's room.  You will not help very much. Just make sure everyone you see has a Damage buff, and drop all other NPC guards and PCs.
<br />

<br />
#5 Battle in the Open.  Stay in the back.  Root everything you see. Drop targets engaged with your friends.  that and hope you are not taken out first.
<br />

<br />
~Wizards are great defenders of keeps, and a single wizard can make a difference.  One time Caer Hurbury was being attacked and I was one of 5 defending the keep. was a 40th season wizard at the time.  I damage buffed every friendly NPC guard.  And I hid behind an arrow slit, dropping everything in range.  I did so well at dropping enemy PC's that they backed off their initial charge.  they reformed again, I switched windows, and they tried once more to setup the ram, I dropped 5 of their group and held off the rest untill reinforcements came to sweep the 24 mids that attacked.  I had a paladin standing behind me, watching for stealthers who would try and get me, he got both of them.  And a cleric to heal/ cure poison when enemy casters hit me with their best shots.  As a fire wizard, You will out damage almost everything you run up against.  Any Elven Hybernian casters actually have less hits than you, you can droppem.  Midguards Magic is slightly weaker (wearing chain and studded does that).  and while it will take a bit more to drop them, you can.
<br />

<br />

<br />
#1 RVR tactic is get the realm ability WILD POWER. and keep it as high as you can.  it is the deciding bonus to finishing off an entire army.
<br />

<br />
#2 Mystic Crystal Lore as soon as you turn level 20.  You should go Thidranki, get realm level 4. and get MCL.  The rest of your days will be power filled and you will never be caught powerless again.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
