				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">I have a Pally and my brother has a Wizard, 23rd level.  He and I work in concert in RvR to deadly results for the Mids and Hibs.  You are right that he is a target for archers and a speedbumb in melee, but when I shadow him, we rock.  I chant heal and he deals long range death in the form of fireballs and other nasties.  We use hit and run tactics all the time and play in BG1 regularly.  Because I am there as a plate clad fighter type looking mean and nasty, very few stealth characters mess with us.  When we are with a war party and archers have other less guarded targets, we usually get 3 or 4 kills and might even make it back to the keep.
<br />

<br />
I would not wait until you get to 30th, go into BG1 and make friends with a fighter type, the meaner looking the better.  have them stick with you all the time, they can't go chasing after a troll or celt or you will die.  Hope this helps.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td class="row1" width="150" align="left" valign="middle"><span class="nav"><a href="#top" class="nav">Back to top</a></span></td>
